Here are both approaches for .NET MAUI Shell navigation with `IQueryAttributable`:

**1. Register the route**
```csharp
// AppShell.xaml.cs
Routing.RegisterRoute("productdetails", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
```

**2. Navigate — string parameter vs. full object**
```csharp
// ProductListViewModel.cs (or code-behind)

// Approach A: pass just the ID
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"productdetails?productId={product.Id}");

// Approach B: pass the full object
var navParams = new Dictionary<string, object>
{
    { "product", product }   // complex object — use the dictionary overload
};
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("productdetails", navParams);
```

**3. Receive data with `IQueryAttributable`**
```csharp
// ProductDetailsViewModel.cs
public partial class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string _productId;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private Product _product;

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach A: string parameter arrives as a string
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var idObj))
        {
            ProductId = idObj?.ToString();
            // Load full product from a service, DB, etc.
            _ = LoadProductAsync(ProductId);
        }

        // Approach B: full object arrives as-is
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var productObj) && productObj is Product p)
        {
            Product = p;
            ProductId = p.Id;
        }
    }

    private async Task LoadProductAsync(string id)
    {
        Product = await _productService.GetByIdAsync(id);
    }
}
```

**4. Wire the ViewModel to the page**
```csharp
// ProductDetailsPage.xaml.cs
public ProductDetailsPage(ProductDetailsViewModel vm)
{
    InitializeComponent();
    BindingContext = vm;
}
```

Shell resolves `IQueryAttributable` on the page's `BindingContext`, so the dictionary is forwarded directly to your ViewModel.

**Key differences:**

| | String param (`?key=val`) | Dictionary overload |
|---|---|---|
| **Data type** | Strings only (URI-encoded) | Any object |
| **Serialization** | Automatic | None — reference passed |
| **Back-navigation** | Survives back-nav | Not replayed on back-nav |
| **Use when** | Simple IDs, flags | You already have the object in memory |
